    "Background": {
      "text": "Infection of brain parenchyma  of the temporal lobes and inferior frontal lobe causing distinct neurologic abnormality\nPathophysiology\nGray matter is predominantly affected (cognitive / psychiatric signs, lethargy, seizure)",
      "subsections": {
        "Microbiology": {
          "text": "HSV\nHZV\nEBV\nCMV\nRabies\nArboviruses (\nWest Nile\n, St. Louis equine) account for 50% of cases\n[1]",
